<subSubSection id="C3079AC0FFEA5F5AE3EEDA9DFBE9FEA3" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA2C94BFFEA5F5AE3EEDA9DFBE9FEA3" blockId="12.[136,1452,158,329]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Notes:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB2C8FFEA5F5AE271DA9CFE62FF53" authorityName="O. V. Morozova, E. S. Popov, T. H. G. Pham &amp; Noordeloos" authorityYear="2022" box="[290,466,158,184]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Entolomataceae" genus="Entoloma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="arion">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFEA5F5AE271DA9CFE62FF53" box="[290,466,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Entoloma arion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily recognized by the bright blue pileus and contrasting white stipe, a very rare combination in subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB2C8FFEA5F5AE2FADAC0FDB8FF37" authorityName="Largent" authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Romagn." box="[425,520,194,220]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Entolomataceae" genus="Entoloma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="12" pageNumber="2" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="section" section="Cyanula">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFEA5F5AE2FADAC0FDB8FF37" box="[425,520,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cyanula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB2C8FFEA5F5AE144DAC0FB85FF37" authority="Corner &amp; E. Horak" authorityName="Corner &amp; E. Horak" box="[535,1077,194,221]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Entolomataceae" genus="Entoloma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="floccosodentatum">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFEA5F5AE144DAC0FCE2FF37" box="[535,850,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Entoloma floccosodentatum</emphasis>
Corner &amp; E. Horak
</taxonomicName>
, in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8CB4BAFFEA5F5AE70DDAC0FA81FF37" author="Horak, E." box="[1118,1329,194,220]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" refId="ref14097" refString="Horak, E. (1980) Entoloma (Agaricales) in Indomalaya and Australasia. Beihefte Nova Hedwigia vol. 65. J. Cramer, Germany, 352 pp." type="book" year="1980">Horak (1980: 288)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F30A89DBFFEA5F5AE625DAC1FF4AFEEB" name="New Caledonia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
is superficially similar in colors, spore size and cystidia form, but its pileus is pale blue and smooth, or only innately fibrillose, or tomentose. The presence of clamps on the hyphae indicates that 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB2C8FFEA5F5AE769DB08FAC3FECF" box="[1082,1395,266,292]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Entolomataceae" genus="Entoloma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="floccosodentatum">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFEA5F5AE769DB08FAC3FECF" box="[1082,1395,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Entoloma floccosodentatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not belong to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1DB2C8FFEA5F5AE2E8DB2CFDAAFEA3" authorityName="Largent" authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Romagn." box="[443,538,302,328]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Entolomataceae" genus="Entoloma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="12" pageNumber="2" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="section" section="Cyanula">
<emphasis id="B9691559FFEA5F5AE2E8DB2CFDAAFEA3" box="[443,538,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cyanula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Geographically it is also very distant and isolated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
